SB103 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to the Alabama Sunset Law; to continue the
5 existence and functioning of the Alabama Construction
6 Recruitment Institute until October 1, 2028, with certain
7 modifications; to require the Alabama Construction Recruitment
8 Institute, the Alabama Department of Workforce, and other
9 interested parties to determine options for the institute to
10 better utilize the administrative and operational services of
11 the department.
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
13 Section 1. Pursuant to the Alabama Sunset Law, the
14 Sunset Committee recommends the continuance of the Alabama
15 Construction Recruitment Institute until October 1, 2028, with
16 additional recommendation for statutory change as set out in
17 Section 3.
18 Section 2. The existence and functioning of the
19 Alabama Construction Recruitment Institute, created and
20 functioning pursuant to Sections 41-10-720 to 41-10-732,
21 inclusive, Code of Alabama 1975, is continued until October 1
22 2028, and those code sections are expressly preserved.
23 Section 3. The Alabama Construction Recruitment
24 Institute, the Alabama Department of Workforce, and other
25 interested parties shall convene to evaluate and determine
26 options to enable the institute to utilize the administrative
27 and operational resources of the department. A report shall be
28 prepared detailing these findings and submitted to the Chair
Page 1

prepared detailing these findings and submitted to the Chair
SB103 Enrolled
29 of the Sunset Committee and other members of the Legislature
30 as deemed appropriate not later than the tenth legislative day
31 of the 2027 Regular Session, at which point all parties shall
32 be absolved of their duties and shall cease meeting.
33 Section 4. The Legislature concurs in the
34 recommendations of the Sunset Committee as provided in
35 Sections 1, 2, and 3.
36 Section 5. This act shall become effective on June 1,
37 2026.
